This paper deals with visualizing and inverting features in object detection, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses algorithms and techniques for feature inversion, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of sparse coding in one of the algorithms suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses diagnosing false positives, which is a common problem in neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper mentions generating high scoring super objects, which could be related to multimedia (cs.MM).
